Troy C. Patton: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 3:10 AM ET
Electrical Equipment

Company Overview of Northern Power Systems Corp.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Troy C. Patton  Director, Northern Power Systems Corp.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 2 different industries.See Board Relationships48$493,414As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Troy C. Patton served as Corporate Development & Business Advisor of Northern Power Systems Corp. and Northern Power Systems, Inc. since August 10, 2016 until January 11, 2017. Mr. Patton served as the Chief Executive Officer at Northern Power Systems Corp. since April 2012 until August 10, 2016 and served as its President until August 10, 2016. He served as Chief Executive Officer of Northern Power Systems, Inc. from April 2012 to August 18, 2016 and its President ... until August 18, 2016. Mr. Patton was wholly responsible for Northern Power Systems' entry into the utility scale marketplace, leading business development as well as Northwind 2.2 engineering, design and manufacturing functions. Mr. Patton has been the Chief Executive Officer at Wind Power Holdings Inc. since April 2012 and serves as its President. Mr. Patton has more than 20 years of experience in the power generation industry. Mr. Patton has experience as a Senior Executive in Wind Power industry, as well as depth of operating experience in the energy industry. He joined Wind Power Holdings in April 2009 as President of the Utility Wind business. During that time, he led Wind Power Holdings' successful development of the NPS 2.3MW permanent magnet direct drive wind turbine. He served as President of Utility Scale Wind at Northern Power Systems since May 5, 2009. Prior to April 2009, he served as Senior Vice President/Head of Engineering and Products at Vestas Wind Systems. Mr. Patton served in numerous technical and leadership roles at General Electric’s Gas Turbine and Wind Turbine businesses and helped facilitate its integration of Enron’s wind energy business in 2003. Earlier in his career, he served as a Load Dispatcher and Engineer on a United States aircraft carrier and United States nuclear submarine, respectively. He serves as a Director of Northern Power Systems, Inc. He has been a Director at Northern Power Systems Corp. since April 2012. He serves as a Director at Wind Power Holdings Inc. Mr. Patton received a Bachelor's Degree in Aerospace and Ocean Engineering from Virginia Tech and a Masters of Business Administration from Clemson University.Read Full Background




