Copyright © 2017 - Patton and Associates, LLC.




Valuation Experts and Consultants


Troy C. Patton, CPA/ABV (Accredited in Business Valuation)


Each Month We Prepare 10-20 Business Valuations Nationwide




Patton & Associates, LLC is managed by Troy C. Patton, CPA/ABV. Troy Patton was named
    the top CPA in public practice by the Indiana CPA Society in 2005. He has been a
    managing partner in public accounting since 1996.  As part of the Business Valuation
    services his team provides expert witness testimony on business valuation issues,
    consults on mergers and acquisitions, provides valuation services, assists with company
    sales and provides valuation services for marital and business divorces.  Our firm
    is one of the leading firms in the US providing business valuation services. By combining
    our expertise, experience and the energy of our staff, each business valuation client
    receives close personal and professional attention. Our high standards, service and
    specialized staff spell the difference between our outstanding performance, and other
    firms. We make sure that every client is served by the expertise of our whole firm.
     We work with many entrepreneurial companies as well as providing valuation assistance
    to the top CPA firms and Companies in the World.





Valuation Services 


Typical reasons to value your business:








Going through a Divorce.


A Gift to family, friend, partner.


Part of Estate Planning


Part of a Bankruptcy proceeding. 


ESOP setup.


IRS 409a 




Complete Confidentiality


Work With You Or Your Accountant


Business Valuations can often involve sensitive issues with spouses, partners, business
    associates, employees and even competitors.  Depending upon your personal situation,
    we can work directly with you so you don’t have to involve your CPA or accountant
    OR we can work with them and keep you informed of the business valuation progress.
     Either way we are discrete and can provide you a level of confidentiality and professionalism
    you may not be able to find locally or can find but do not want the rumors or speculation
    working with a local resource can generate.






