Helpful

helpful
local insight was helpful






Dennis Meier
                  
                  on 09/15/2016
                  
                
Troy IL - Small Town Charm


                    
                    Troy's small town charm along with convenient location to big city business helped Troy grow to the third fastest growing area in the U.S. by 1978, and still shows no signs of...
                    
                    more


                    Troy's small town charm along with convenient location to big city business helped Troy grow to the third fastest growing area in the U.S. by 1978, and still shows no signs of slowing down. Despite the continued growth, Troy has maintained its small town charm. A strong sense of community combined with the promise of opportunity makes Troy a unique and wonderful place to live.

Troy is ideally placed to offer the lifestyle of a neighborhood community while having quick and easy access to many of the exciting cultural and entertainment activities, as well as numerous business and educational opportunities available in the surrounding Metro East area.

Troy is centrally located in the St. Louis Metro East area, approximately 20 minutes from downtown St. Louis, Mo with direct access to I-55, I-70, I-270, U.S. Route 40 and U.S. Route 162.

The schools are rated high and average list price of a home is $229,498 and  average selling price is $190,954

                    less















Real Estate Market Trends in Troy, IL

    The median price home price in Troy is $234,900. Right now, there are 83 homes listed for sale in Troy, including 0 condos and 0 foreclosures. You can research home values, browse Troy's hottest homes, and see what Coldwell Banker's agents have to say about the local area. Check out our page on Troy market trends  to start exploring!
  











